928
00:36:28,686 --> 00:36:30,888
Tell him about
Coca-Cola colonialism.

929
00:36:30,889 --> 00:36:31,888
What?

930
00:36:31,889 --> 00:36:33,323
As chairman Khrushchev said...

931
00:36:33,324 --> 00:36:35,525
on the 40th anniversary
of the revolution...

932
00:36:35,526 --> 00:36:38,791
To hell with the revolution
and to hell with Khrushchev!

933
00:36:40,498 --> 00:36:42,762
The hell with Frank Sinatra.

934
00:36:43,401 --> 00:36:45,069
Oh, it's gonna be
a real clambake...

935
00:36:45,070 --> 00:36:46,737
when your folks
get here tomorrow.

936
00:36:46,738 --> 00:36:48,972
How are we gonna explain this?

937
00:36:48,973 --> 00:36:52,076
That's your problem
because I won't be here.

938
00:36:52,077 --> 00:36:53,710
What do you mean,
you won't be here?

939
00:36:53,711 --> 00:36:56,647
Tonight, my wife and I
are leaving for Moscow.

940
00:36:56,648 --> 00:36:58,481
Moscow?

941
00:36:58,482 --> 00:37:01,285
That's what I came to tell you.
He's got a scholarship...

942
00:37:01,286 --> 00:37:03,671
to the People's
Technological Institute.

943
00:37:03,672 --> 00:37:06,057
He's studying to be
a missile engineer.

944
00:37:06,058 --> 00:37:07,649
Soviet missiles...

945
00:37:08,859 --> 00:37:10,760
Venus!

946
00:37:10,761 --> 00:37:12,092
American missiles...

947
00:37:12,997 --> 00:37:15,056
Miami Beach.

948
00:37:17,435 --> 00:37:21,806
So you just tell Daddy
I'm on my way to the U.S.S.R.

949
00:37:21,807 --> 00:37:23,967
That's short for Russia.

950
00:37:26,344 --> 00:37:28,496
Are you out of your
seventeen-year-old mind?

951
00:37:28,497 --> 00:37:30,648
Russia's to get out of,
not to get into.

952
00:37:30,649 --> 00:37:32,400
Where Otto goes, I go!

953
00:37:32,401 --> 00:37:34,027
You just try to stop us.

954
00:37:34,028 --> 00:37:35,652
Can you talk to your wife?

955
00:37:35,653 --> 00:37:37,755
Well, I certainly
can't talk to them.

956
00:37:37,756 --> 00:37:38,881
On this phone.

957
00:37:41,192 --> 00:37:42,727
Hello? Yes, dear.

958
00:37:42,728 --> 00:37:44,261
Mac, hold everything.

959
00:37:44,262 --> 00:37:45,896
I bet I know
what happened to Scarlett.

960
00:37:45,897 --> 00:37:48,498
Lucky Pierre
must be back in town.

961
00:37:48,499 --> 00:37:51,936
It's not Lucky Pierre.
It's Crazy Otto.

962
00:37:51,937 --> 00:37:53,003
Are you ready for this?

963
00:37:53,004 --> 00:37:55,472
She's married. That's right.

964
00:37:55,473 --> 00:37:57,441
She got herself an ever-loving,
curly-haired...

965
00:37:57,442 --> 00:37:59,272
card-carrying husband.

966
00:38:00,411 --> 00:38:02,641
She married a Communist?

967
00:38:03,147 --> 00:38:05,763
This is gonna be the biggest
thing to hit Atlanta...

968
00:38:05,764 --> 00:38:08,379
since General Sherman
threw that little barbecue.

969
00:38:09,086 --> 00:38:10,644
No, I don't think it's funny.

970
00:38:11,222 --> 00:38:14,792
They're gonna live in Moscow?
Now, that's funny.

971
00:38:14,793 --> 00:38:17,261
Yeah, hysterical,
but what can I do...

972
00:38:17,262 --> 00:38:18,713
go fight the Kremlin?

973
00:38:18,714 --> 00:38:20,163
