974
00:38:20,164 --> 00:38:21,731
They're young,
they're in love...

975
00:38:21,732 --> 00:38:24,234
and we're a dead herring
in the moonlight...

976
00:38:24,235 --> 00:38:28,005
so who am I to stand in the way
of a happy Socialist marriage?

977
00:38:28,006 --> 00:38:30,024
Oh, come off it, Mac.
I know you.

978
00:38:30,025 --> 00:38:32,043
You've got something
up your sleeve.

979
00:38:32,044 --> 00:38:35,171
I wouldn't be surprised. Bye.

980
00:38:35,813 --> 00:38:38,349
Now, what time
are you kids leaving?

981
00:38:38,350 --> 00:38:40,101
7:00 on the Moscow Express.

982
00:38:40,102 --> 00:38:41,851
Why do you want to know?

983
00:38:41,852 --> 00:38:43,787
Because I'm gonna
dynamite the train.

984
00:38:43,788 --> 00:38:45,722
What makes you guys
so suspicious?

985
00:38:45,723 --> 00:38:48,776
I better get back to the house
and start packing.

986
00:38:48,777 --> 00:38:51,604
You think I ought to take
both my mink coats?

987
00:38:51,605 --> 00:38:54,303
Darling, no woman
should have two mink coats...

988
00:38:54,304 --> 00:38:56,787
until every woman in the world
has one mink coat.

989
00:38:56,788 --> 00:38:59,270
Cut the other one up
and make him a pair of shorts.

990
00:38:59,271 --> 00:39:01,072
I hear it's freezing there
all the time.

991
00:39:01,073 --> 00:39:02,273
Thirty below zero.

992
00:39:02,274 --> 00:39:03,640
Fascist lies!

993
00:39:03,641 --> 00:39:05,543
You better go home
and pack, too, darling.

994
00:39:05,544 --> 00:39:06,910
It will take me no time.

995
00:39:06,911 --> 00:39:09,680
Just my chessboard, my extra
shirt, and two hundred books.

996
00:39:09,681 --> 00:39:12,450
As long as Smiley here
is going back to East Berlin...

997
00:39:12,451 --> 00:39:13,683
I'll get the car for you.

998
00:39:13,684 --> 00:39:15,185
Schlemmer, will you
run downstairs...

999
00:39:15,186 --> 00:39:17,711
and tell Fritz he'll have
to take Scarlett home?

1000
00:39:18,422 --> 00:39:19,790
You're letting her go to Moscow?

1001
00:39:19,791 --> 00:39:21,024
In a pig's eye.

1002
00:39:21,025 --> 00:39:23,426
Now, look.
His motorcycle's downstairs.

1003
00:39:23,427 --> 00:39:25,725
Remember that idea
you had about the balloon?

1004
00:39:27,932 --> 00:39:29,065
Just think, Liebchen...

1005
00:39:29,066 --> 00:39:31,869
tomorrow night, we'll be
strolling hand in hand...

1006
00:39:31,870 --> 00:39:33,570
across Red Square.

1007
00:39:33,571 --> 00:39:34,605
I hope you won't be
ashamed of me...

1008
00:39:34,606 --> 00:39:36,207
in front of your friends.

1009
00:39:36,208 --> 00:39:37,407
Of course not.

1010
00:39:37,408 --> 00:39:40,094
I promise you, I'll only wear
my jewelry at home.

1011
00:39:40,095 --> 00:39:42,780
They have assigned us
a magnificent apartment...

1012
00:39:42,781 --> 00:39:44,682
just a short walk
from the bathroom.

1013
00:39:44,683 --> 00:39:45,782
I love you.

1014
00:39:45,783 --> 00:39:47,450
I'll make you very happy.

1015
00:39:47,451 --> 00:39:49,587
Every morning, we'll have
breakfast in bed.

1016
00:39:49,588 --> 00:39:50,920
Sounds wonderful.

1017
00:39:50,921 --> 00:39:52,623
Also lunch, also dinner.

1018
00:39:52,624 --> 00:39:53,890
In bed?

1019
00:39:53,891 --> 00:39:55,393
There's no table and no chairs.

1020
00:39:55,394 --> 00:39:56,724
Who cares?

1021
00:40:00,097 --> 00:40:01,998
I'll pick you at 6:20 sharp...

